title: Kourtney Kardashian thanks doctors for 'saving baby's life' after foetal surgery
description: Kourtney Kardashian has revealed she is recovering from urgent foetal surgery as she praised doctors for "saving" her baby's life.

title: Villages cut off after 'Biblical' downpours in Greece as state of emergency remains in place
description: The rain that Storm Daniel has brought to parts of Greece is never-ending.

title: Researchers take major step towards creating synthetic embryo-like structures
description: Researchers have taken a major step towards creating synthetic embryo-like structures that mimic real human embryos with most of the fundamental features of the earliest stages of life.

title: Women taking painkillers while on the pill could face greater risk of blood clots, study suggests
description: Women are being warned that taking some common painkillers while using the contraceptive pill may increase their risk of suffering blood clots.

title: Four 1,900-year-old Roman swords found in incredible Dead Sea cave discovery
description: Four exquisitely-preserved Roman swords have been found after 1,900 years in a cave near the Dead Sea.

title: Inside the trial of man accused of being key figure in Channel 'migrant smuggling group'
description: It was a sunny place to discuss dark crimes.

title: Jenni Hermoso files complaint over 'unsolicited kiss' at World Cup
description: Jenni Hermoso has filed a complaint with the prosecutor's office over an "unsolicited kiss" by Spanish FA chief Luis Rubiales following the Women's World Cup final.

title: Man arrested after trying to run from Florida to London in a makeshift hamster wheel
description: A Florida man who tried to run across the Atlantic Ocean to London using a makeshift hamster wheel has been arrested.

title: Parenting advice YouTuber charged with child abuse amid torture claims
description: A former YouTuber who gave parenting advice online has been charged with six counts of aggravated child abuse after two of her six children were found to be abused and malnourished.

title: New Airbnb rules in New York limit accommodation options for tourists
description: Holidaymakers searching for accommodation in New York City will find far fewer options than usual after a clampdown on Airbnb rules.

title: Tax fossil fuels and flying to pay for climate action in Africa, leaders urge
description: Leaders of African nations needing to pay for expensive climate measures have called for a new global tax on polluting industries like fossil fuels, shipping and aviation to help raise funds.

title: Sailors heading to Australia rescued after sharks attack boat
description: Three sailors have been rescued from a floating catamaran left badly damaged by shark attacks more than 500 miles (804km) off the Australian coast.

title: 'You were right, I was wrong': Author apologises to Father Ted writer for criticism over trans issues
description: Author John Boyne, who previously criticised TV writer Graham Linehan over his stance on trans issues, has issued a public apology, saying: "You were right, I was wrong."

title: Britons stranded as deadly rainstorms batter Greece and Turkey
description: Britons chasing a bit of late summer sun have been caught up in deadly rainstorms that have battered Greece, Turkey and Bulgaria.

title: Cyclone kills at least 21 in Brazil - as woman dies during rescue attempt
description: A cyclone has killed at least 21 people and left hundreds more homeless in southern Brazil.

title: Manchester United release statement after Antony abuse allegations
description: Manchester United have said they are taking allegations against Antony "seriously" after the player was accused of abuse by his former girlfriend.

title: Sara Sharif's stepmother says family 'willing to co-operate' with UK authorities
description: The stepmother of Sara Sharif, the 10-year-old girl found dead at her home last month, has spoken for the first time in a video shared with Sky News and said the family is willing to co-operate with British authorities and  "fight our case in court".
